[[File:Bradford UK local election 1984 map.png|right|thumb|500px|Map of the results for the 1984 Bradford council election.]]
The '''[[City of Bradford Metropolitan District Council]] elections''' were held on Thursday, 3 May 1984, with one third of the council and an extra vacancy in [[Bradford Moor]] to be elected. The council remained under [[no overall control]].<ref name="results">{{cite news |title=District results: Bradford |work=[[The Yorkshire Post]] |page= |date=4 May 1984}}</ref><ref name="BBC">{{Cite web| url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/special/vote2012/council/E08000032.stm | title = Vote 2012: Bradford | accessdate = 2013-02-20 | publisher = ''[[BBC News Online]]''}}</ref>

